Enslin is an extraordinary celebrity chef who will keep you amused while sharing all his cooking secrets. He believes fresh ingredients and an infusion of simple flavours is the way to delight everyone. He effortlessly prepares the most exceptional food, perfect for every occasion.  Tippie’s Chorizo Prawns 1kg prawns 1 cup water 1 chorizo, sliced Toothpicks 1 tsp olive oil 1 tsp chilli flakes 1 tbs fish sauce 2 tbs honey  Parsley, finely chopped  Method Heat oven to 180ºC. Shell the prawns. Place the heads in a medium-sized pot, add water and simmer for 10 minutes. Cut the chorizo slices in half. Place chorizo in the curve of the prawn, secure with a toothpick. Drizzle olive oil over the prawns, place into the oven for 5 minutes. Place the heads in a strainer and crush with the back of a spoon to extract the juices. Return juices to the stove add chilli flakes, fish sauce and honey. Allow to reduce. Remove prawns from the oven, drizzle reduction over prawns, place them back in the oven for 5 minutes. Serve hot or cold, garnished with parsley. The Saturday Star